he claims and aspirations of political religions, especially when they conflict so deeply with liberal norms and practices, and he suggests how liberal critics can speak confidently in ways that respect cultural and religious difference.Miller explores other concerns within these investigations as well, such as the protection of human rights and a liberal democratic commitment to multicultural politics. In relating religion and ethics, he develops a new lens for viewing political religions and their moral responsibilities. This probing inquiry also forces us to rethink our response to 9/11.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aHuman rights. 0aLiberalism. 0aPolitical violence. 0aTerrorismxReligious aspects. 0aTolerationxReligious aspects. 0aViolencexReligious aspects. 0aWarxReligious aspects. 7aRELIGION / Religious Intolerance, Persecution & Conflict.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066254208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045952440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/mill15098423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231521864.jpg  a978-3-11-044247-2  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013  a978-3-11-045952-4  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066254-2  CUP eBook Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG